OL,3,C'I'm still waiting for justice': The
OL,4,Cwomen fighting for pension compensation
OL,6,F"I'm 70 in June, and I'm still waiting
OL,7,Ffor justice."
OL,9,FJune Roy, from Newcastle, is among
OL,10,Fthousands of women born in the 1950s,
OL,11,Fhit hardest by the rise of the state
OL,12,Fpension age.
OL,14,F"We started campaigning, and it went
OL,15,Fon and on, and we were just being
OL,16,Fignored all the time," she said.
OL,18,F"I was so angry.. the unfairness and
OL,19,Finjustice of it all... We didn't count
OL,20,Fback then, and we still don't count."
