OL,3,C'I'm still waiting for justice': The
OL,4,Cwomen fighting for pension compensation
OL,6,FThe group of women born in the 1950s
OL,7,Fknown as 'women' (Women Against State
OL,8,FPension Inequality) have said that the
OL,9,Frise in the state pension age in 1995
OL,10,Fled them to suffer financially.
OL,12,FThe 1995 Pensions Act and subsequent
OL,13,Flegislation raised the state pension
OL,14,Fage for women born on or after 6 April
OL,15,F1950 from 60 to 65, then further to 66
OL,16,F- making it the same as the men's
OL,17,Fstate pension age.
